sizeof(delims) determines the size of delims in bytes, which can be n=16 (4x4) on 32-bit and n=32 (4x8) on 64-bit systems. So we need:
for(unsigned int i=0; i < sizeof(delims) / sizeof(delims[0]); i++)
instead of
for(unsigned int i=0; i < sizeof(delims); i++)
I will submit a PR.

